The paper deals with pedestrian detection using deep learning techniques, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) category. The proposed method involves designing a new loss function and pooling unit, which involves optimization and machine learning techniques, respectively, making it likely to belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories. The paper also deals with object detection in crowded scenes, which involves robotics and automation, making it likely to belong to the robotics (cs.RO) category. Finally, the paper deals with pedestrian detection datasets, which involves multimedia (cs.MM) applications.
